reviewText: Great movie shot in Ottumwa Iowa
I got this for my mother-in-law.  She was going with Tom Arnold's brother at the time, and it was filmed in Ottumwa, IA, where Tom is from.  She loves this movie.  Don't know why.
Kind of "corny" but I loved it .... love Roseanne & Tom, I guess that's why.

Roseanne Barr is one of my favorite comediens and she is in her sarcastic corny self as the woman who loved Elvis. This movie is not award winning, but it helps you get through the day with a laugh or two!

I do!....this is a fun family film about a character who is a big Elvis Presley fan and wants to do charitable work in his name, this was Roseanne's second try at a t.v. movie of the week, her first one titled Backfield in Motion (also on vhs) which I found more entertaining but this one was just as enjoyable and is a great vhs for any fan ot the domestic goddess

this is a feel good movie. i am from south east iowa and most people are loving and thoughtful. joyce [rosanna]is the same way my sister and i are. my sister is the poorest person i know and she would give the coat of her back to someone that needed it,and have seen her do it. this movie met alot more to me than just a movie. if more people were like joyce and my sister nancy this world would be a better place. watch this movie and learn from it.

I absolutely loved this movie.  I myself am from Ottumwa Iowa where the film was shot.  I guess that made it all the more wonderful.  Roseanne does a great job, as well as Ms. Gibb.  Lighthearted family entertainment!
